##Exercise 1 5.2.1

Table 1 in 5.2 shows us countries and their cases of turberculosis in different years. Columns are: country, year of observance, cases in that year, population of the country in that year Table 2 shows us the same values but has 2 rows for 1 year, serparating counts and population into those 2 rows. Table 3 shows us the same values but combines TB cases and population into 1 observance, TB/Population size

##Exercise 2 5.2.1

Code 
table2_wide <- pivot_wider(table2, names_from = type, values_from = count)

table2_wide <- mutate(table2_wide, rate = (cases / population) * 10000)

table3_split <- separate(table3, rate, into = c("cases", "population"), sep = "/")

table3_split <- mutate(table3_split,
                       cases = as.numeric(cases),
                       population = as.numeric(population))

table3_split <- mutate(table3_split, rate_calc = (cases / population) * 10000)

library(tidyverse)
library(lubridate)

#| eval: false
download.file(
  url = "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/CSSEGISandData/COVID-19/master/csse_covid_19_data/csse_covid_19_time_series/time_series_covid19_confirmed_global.csv",
  destfile = "data/time_series_covid19_confirmed_global.csv"
)

time_series_confirmed <- read_csv("data/time_series_covid19_confirmed_global.csv") |> 
  rename(
    Province_State = `Province/State`,
    Country_Region = `Country/Region`
  )

time_series_confirmed_long <- time_series_confirmed |> 
  pivot_longer(
    cols = -c(Province_State, Country_Region, Lat, Long),
    names_to = "Date",
    values_to = "Confirmed"
  )

time_series_confirmed_long <- time_series_confirmed_long |> 
  mutate(Date = mdy(Date))

Exercise 3

Code 
time_series_confirmed_long_daily <- time_series_confirmed_long |>
  group_by(Country_Region, Date) |>
  summarise(Confirmed = sum(Confirmed)) |>
  mutate(Daily = Confirmed - lag(Confirmed, default = first(Confirmed)))
time_series_confirmed_long_daily |>
  filter(Country_Region %in% c("US", "Italy", "France", "Brazil", "India")) |>
  ggplot(aes(x = Date, y = Daily, color = Country_Region)) +
    geom_line() +
    ggtitle("Daily COVID-19 Confirmed Cases")

Exercise 4

Code 
# Read and tidy
time_series_deaths_confirmed <- read_csv("data/time_series_covid19_deaths_global.csv") |>
  rename(
    Province_State = "Province/State",
    Country_Region = "Country/Region"
  )

time_series_deaths_long <- time_series_deaths_confirmed |>
  pivot_longer(
    -c(Province_State, Country_Region, Lat, Long),
    names_to = "Date",
    values_to = "Deaths"
  )

# Convert Date column to proper date format
time_series_deaths_long$Date <- mdy(time_series_deaths_long$Date)

# Summarize by country and date
time_series_deaths_long_summary <- time_series_deaths_long |>
  group_by(Country_Region, Date) |>
  summarise(Deaths = sum(Deaths), .groups = "drop")

# Plot cumulative deaths for US, Canada, Mexico
time_series_deaths_long_summary |>
  filter(Country_Region %in% c("US", "Canada", "Mexico")) |>
  ggplot(aes(x = Date, y = Deaths, color = Country_Region)) +
    geom_line() +
    ggtitle("Cumulative COVID-19 Deaths: US, Canada, Mexico")

Exercise 5

Code 
library(tidyverse)
library(lubridate)

# Step 1: Read and tidy deaths data (if not already done)
time_series_deaths_confirmed <- read_csv("data/time_series_covid19_deaths_global.csv") |>
  rename(
    Province_State = "Province/State",
    Country_Region = "Country/Region"
  )

time_series_deaths_long <- time_series_deaths_confirmed |>
  pivot_longer(
    -c(Province_State, Country_Region, Lat, Long),
    names_to = "Date",
    values_to = "Deaths"
  )

time_series_deaths_long$Date <- mdy(time_series_deaths_long$Date)

# Step 2: Summarize by country/date and calculate daily deaths
time_series_deaths_long_daily <- time_series_deaths_long |>
  group_by(Country_Region, Date) |>
  summarise(Deaths = sum(Deaths), .groups = "drop") |>
  mutate(Daily_Deaths = Deaths - lag(Deaths, default = first(Deaths)))

# Step 3: Plot daily deaths for countries of your choice
time_series_deaths_long_daily |>
  filter(Country_Region %in% c("US", "Canada", "Mexico", "Brazil", "India")) |>
  ggplot(aes(x = Date, y = Daily_Deaths, color = Country_Region)) +
    geom_line() +
    ggtitle("Daily COVID-19 Deaths")

Exercise 6

Code 
library(gganimate)
library(gifski)
theme_set(theme_bw())

# Choose a few countries for the animation
daily_deaths <- time_series_deaths_long_daily |>
  filter(Country_Region %in% c("US", "Canada", "Mexico", "Brazil", "India"))

# Build the plot
p <- ggplot(daily_deaths, aes(x = Date, y = Daily_Deaths, color = Country_Region)) +
  geom_line() +
  ggtitle("Daily COVID-19 Deaths") +
  transition_reveal(Date)

# Render the animation
animate(p, renderer = gifski_renderer(), end_pause = 15)
Code 
# Save as gif (optional)
anim_save("daily_deaths_animation.gif", p)
